  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      SSRI's has been demonstrated to be partially effective in schizophrenia and OCD. We therefore
      suggest that Escitalopram up to 20 mg /d in those patients could be effective in reducing
      obsessive compulsive symptomatology
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
